In this press gaggle, Principal Deputy Press Secretary Eric Schultz provides updates on various topics. He mentions that eight countries have pledged at least $300 million in financial contributions to tackle the Ebola virus in West Africa. He also discusses the role of Ron Klain, who will be coordinating the administration's Ebola response. Schultz confirms that Klain will be paid for his role. Other topics addressed include the President's schedule, travel bans, the issue of Nazi war criminals receiving Social Security payments, and concerns about easing sanctions on Iran. The press gaggle concludes with a mention of potential additional funding from Congress for Ebola response efforts.